    "summary": "Reza is a researcher in the field of cyber-physical systems. He is currently doing his Ph.D. in the field of integrating safety and cybersecurity at the University of Twente in the Netherlands. Before that, he did research in the field of trustworthy Cyber-Physical Systems for one year at the University of Southern Denmark. Also, he had an M.Sc. from the University of Tabriz. During his M.Sc. education period, he worked on Network Security, and more specifically, security of the Internet of Things. He has nearly a year of expertise and industrial employment history in IoT and smart metering. He worked with open source IoT operating system, with support for NBIoT, LoRaWAN, BLE, NFC, and other communications stacks and developed projects in Arm Mbed OS which is a free, open-source embedded operating system designed specifically for the \u201cthings\u201d in the Internet of Things. He is also active in the industry. Currently he\u2019s the Co-founder & CTO of a company in the Netherlands, which provides an easy-to-use VPS.",
